  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. Evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Intended use is limited to comparative ranking of operating points for hemolysis risk under adult CPB flow conditions (3–6 L/min, 60–120 mmHg differential pressure). Decision scope, device class, and patient population are described in the Requirement and Claim nodes bound below.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/cfd-hemolysis-gcbp-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-gcbp-piv-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-gcbp-hemolysis-bench"
  ],
